# CODEOWNERS — WorldSim
#
# Pre-contributor phase governance note
# ──────────────────────────────────────
# WorldSim is currently developed by a single Engineering Lead (@PublicEnemage).
# All ownership rules below resolve to the same individual. This is a known
# governance gap — genuine separation of duties requires at least two principals
# with distinct merge and exception authorities.
#
# This file exists now, before external contributors join, for two reasons:
#
# 1. Structural habit. CODEOWNERS enforces review routing once a second
#    principal exists. Establishing the patterns now means the machinery
#    is in place when it matters, rather than retrofitted under deadline
#    pressure at the moment a contributor submits a PR to the simulation
#    engine core.
#
# 2. Tooling readiness. GitHub uses CODEOWNERS to populate PR review
#    requirements, branch protection rules, and the code review audit trail.
#    These mechanisms take effect immediately when a second owner is added
#    to a path — but only if the file and the branch protection rules referencing
#    it already exist.
#
# The governance gap is documented in CLAUDE.md § Governance and addressed
# through the intended governance progression described there. Self-approved
# exceptions during the single-principal phase are required to document the
# limitation explicitly in the exception record.
#
# When a second principal joins:
# 1. Add them to the specific paths that match their domain (simulation engine,
#    data standards, infrastructure, etc.)
# 2. Enable "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection for main
# 3. Update CLAUDE.md § Governance to reflect the actual separation achieved
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Global default — all files not matched by a more specific rule
* @PublicEnemage

# docs/ — standards, ADRs, compliance, and policy documents
# Changes to these files define what the codebase must do; they require
# the same explicit review as the code itself.
/docs/ @PublicEnemage

# Simulation engine core — highest architectural sensitivity
# models.py is ADR-001 made concrete. Changes here ripple to every module
# that will ever be written. Interface changes require an ADR update in
# the same PR.
/backend/app/simulation/engine/ @PublicEnemage

# Project constitution
# CLAUDE.md governs every agent session and every architectural decision.
# Any change requires Engineering Lead review regardless of who proposes it.
/CLAUDE.md @PublicEnemage

# Workflow and governance configuration
# GitHub Actions, issue templates, labels, and branch protection config.
# Changes here affect CI integrity and the compliance audit trail.
/.github/ @PublicEnemage
